<TITLE> Transmission glitches disrupt internet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 3 (bdnews24.com)Technical glitches with the transmission line of Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Limited disrupted internet connections for hours Thursday, a BTCL official said. "The faults have been fixed and internet connections have been restored," Mir Md Murshed, deputy director of BTCL's public relations wing, told bdnews24.com by phone. Meanwhile, National Phone, an ISP, sent a message to its clients Thursday that it was providing services through alternative connections. The BTCL official said that there were no problems with the submarine cable. "The faults were with the transmission line." bdn
